{%- comment -%}
  PDP CSS — above-fold files load eager (parser-blocking) because
  they style the LCP candidate (gallery main image), price, swatches,
  and the ATC button which sit above the fold on every product
  page. Accordion is below-fold (merchant description / shipping /
  returns copy) so its CSS loads async via the media="print"→all
  swap pattern — same trick theme.liquid uses for drawer/overlay
  CSS. Saves one parser-blocking round-trip on 4G mobile.

  noscript fallback ensures the accordion is styled when JavaScript
  is disabled (no onload event fires without JS).
{%- endcomment -%}
{{ 'kt-section-main-product.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{{ 'kt-product-gallery.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{{ 'kt-product-price.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{{ 'kt-product-variant-picker.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{{ 'kt-product-form.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<link
  rel="stylesheet"
  href="{{ 'kt-product-accordion.css' | asset_url }}"
  media="print"
  onload="this.media='all'"
>
<noscript>{{ 'kt-product-accordion.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}</noscript>

{%- assign main_product_countdown_label_default = 'kt.product.countdown.limited_time' | t -%}
{%- assign main_product_sample_header_default = 'kt.section.product_showroom.sample_header_default' | t -%}
{%- assign main_product_add_sample_default = 'kt.section.product_showroom.add_sample_default' | t -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Main Product — E-commerce PDP.
  Ported from product/[id]/page.tsx but refactored so every element in
  the info column is a merchant-editable block. The order of blocks in
  the theme editor drives the order on the page; merchants can add,
  remove, and rearrange title, price, meta, countdown, description,
  variant picker, buy buttons, trust-badge group, sample-order box
  (from showroom), and accordions.

  Left column (58%): fixed gallery (not block-driven; always visible).
  Right column (42%): sticky info pane built entirely from blocks.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign current_variant = product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}

<section class="kt-pdp" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}" data-section-type="main-product">
  {%- comment -%}
    Breadcrumb at the very top of the PDP — sits between the
    header above and the gallery + info layout below, so the
    navigation trail is the first thing the shopper sees on the
    product page (collection → product name). Gated by the
    theme-global `settings.kt_show_breadcrumbs` toggle.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if settings.kt_show_breadcrumbs -%}
    {%- render 'breadcrumbs', class_extra: 'kt-breadcrumbs-wrap' -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  <div class="page-width">
    <div class="kt-pdp__layout">

      {%- comment -%} LEFT: Gallery {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="kt-pdp__gallery-col">
        {%- render 'product-media-gallery', product: product -%}
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} RIGHT: Info — block-driven {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="kt-pdp__info-col">
        <div class="kt-pdp__info-sticky" data-kt-pdp-anim-group>

          {%- comment -%}
            Breadcrumb moved out — see the kt-pdp top of section, above
            the gallery + info layout. Keeping it inside the sticky info
            column (where it lived before) tucked it into a narrow
            right-rail context where shoppers couldn't see it as a
            navigation aid. The user reported "no breadcrumb on PDP"
            for that reason. The theme-global `settings.kt_show_breadcrumbs`
            gates visibility; merchants who want a quieter PDP turn it off
            in Theme settings → Layout.
          {%- endcomment -%}

          {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
            {%- case block.type -%}

              {%- when 'title' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  R146 HEADING-TAG-LOCK-1: PDP MUST emit an <h1>
                  for SEO + WCAG 2.4.6. Schema permits merchant
                  override (h1/h2) for layout flexibility but a
                  product page without an h1 is a hard Theme Store
                  reject. Force `h1` regardless of the block setting
                  when this is the product title block (the page's
                  primary heading). Schema setting kept for
                  backward compatibility — value ignored here.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- assign heading_tag = 'h1' -%}
                <{{ heading_tag }} class="kt-pdp__title" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>{{ product.title | escape }}</{{ heading_tag }}>
                {%- comment -%}
                  Variant SKU rendered for B2B / wholesale shoppers and
                  inventory tracking — Theme Store Section 7 expects SKU
                  visible and updated on variant change. JS in
                  assets/product-form.js refreshes [data-product-sku]
                  on variant select.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- if product.selected_or_first_available_variant.sku != blank -%}
                  <p class="kt-pdp__sku" data-product-sku>
                    <span class="visually-hidden">{{ 'kt.product.sku.label' | t | default: 'SKU' }}: </span>
                    {{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.sku | escape }}
                  </p>
                {%- else -%}
                  <p class="kt-pdp__sku" data-product-sku hidden>
                    <span class="visually-hidden">{{ 'kt.product.sku.label' | t | default: 'SKU' }}: </span>
                  </p>
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'meta' -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__meta" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- if block.settings.show_rating -%}
                    {%- render 'product-rating', product: product -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.show_rating and block.settings.show_stock -%}
                    <span class="kt-pdp__meta-sep" aria-hidden="true">|</span>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.show_stock -%}
                    {%- comment -%}
                      R122 — three-state stock indicator with low-stock
                      "Only N left" messaging when:
                      1. Variant has Shopify-managed inventory
                      2. Has stock left (>0)
                      3. Stock count is at-or-below the merchant-set
                         threshold (settings.kt_low_stock_threshold)
                      4. Merchant has the kt_show_low_stock toggle on
                      Real inventory (not deceptive/fake counter) —
                      Theme Store rule allows this when backed by
                      Shopify's actual inventory_quantity.
                    {%- endcomment -%}
                    {%- assign show_low_stock = false -%}
                    {%- if settings.kt_show_low_stock and current_variant.available and current_variant.inventory_management == 'shopify' and current_variant.inventory_quantity > 0 and current_variant.inventory_quantity <= settings.kt_low_stock_threshold -%}
                      {%- assign show_low_stock = true -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                    {%- if show_low_stock -%}
                      <span class="kt-pdp__stock kt-pdp__stock--low" role="status">{{ 'kt.product.low_stock_html' | t: count: current_variant.inventory_quantity | default: 'Only a few left' }}</span>
                    {%- elsif current_variant.available -%}
                      <span class="kt-pdp__stock kt-pdp__stock--in">{{ 'kt.product.in_stock' | t | default: 'In Stock' }}</span>
                    {%- else -%}
                      <span class="kt-pdp__stock kt-pdp__stock--out">{{ 'kt.product.sold_out' | t }}</span>
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'vendor' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  Vendor block — Theme Store: "Themes must support blocks
                  for all or most elements on the main section of the
                  product page (product price, vendor, description as
                  individual blocks)". Linked to the vendor's collection
                  by Shopify convention so customers can browse the rest
                  of that maker's catalogue with one click; merchants who
                  treat vendor as a brand category get free cross-product
                  navigation. The block self-suppresses when product.vendor
                  is blank (Shopify allows vendor-less products) so the
                  PDP doesn't emit an empty link.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- if product.vendor != blank -%}
                  <div class="kt-pdp__vendor" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                    {%- if block.settings.show_label -%}
                      <span class="kt-pdp__vendor-label">{{ 'kt.product.vendor_label' | t | default: 'By' }}</span>
                    {%- endif -%}
                    <a href="{{ product.vendor | url_for_vendor }}" class="kt-pdp__vendor-link">
                      {{ product.vendor | escape }}
                    </a>
                  </div>
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'countdown' -%}
                {%- assign deal_ends_at = product.metafields.custom.deal_ends_at.value -%}
                {%- if deal_ends_at != blank -%}
                  <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-block" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                    <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
                    <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-top">
                      <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-label">
                        <span class="kt-pdp__countdown-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <span>{{ block.settings.label }}</span>
                      </div>
                      {%- if block.settings.badge != blank -%}
                        <span class="kt-pdp__countdown-badge">{{ block.settings.badge }}</span>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    </div>
                    <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-bottom">
                      <div
                        class="kt-pdp__countdown-timer"
                        data-countdown
                        data-ends-at="{{ deal_ends_at | date: '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S%z' }}"
                        aria-label="{{ block.settings.label | default: main_product_countdown_label_default | escape }}"
                      >
                        <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-unit"><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-num" data-countdown-days>00</span><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-key">D</span></div>
                        <span class="kt-pdp__countdown-colon">:</span>
                        <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-unit"><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-num" data-countdown-hours>00</span><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-key">H</span></div>
                        <span class="kt-pdp__countdown-colon">:</span>
                        <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-unit"><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-num" data-countdown-minutes>00</span><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-key">M</span></div>
                        <span class="kt-pdp__countdown-colon">:</span>
                        <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-unit"><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-num" data-countdown-seconds>00</span><span class="kt-pdp__countdown-key">S</span></div>
                      </div>
                      {%- if block.settings.ending_label != blank -%}
                        <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-ends">
                          <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-ends-label">{{ block.settings.ending_label }}</div>
                          <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-progress"><div class="kt-pdp__countdown-progress-fill"></div></div>
                        </div>
                      {%- else -%}
                        <div class="kt-pdp__countdown-progress"><div class="kt-pdp__countdown-progress-fill"></div></div>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    </div>
                  </div>
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'price' -%}
                <div {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- render 'product-price', product: product -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'description' -%}
                {%- if product.description != blank -%}
                  {%- comment -%}
                    `rte` class is critical for Theme Store: "All
                    RTE-generated content must be consistent across
                    templates" (h1-h6, blockquote, ul/ol, links). Without
                    it, the product description here renders with the
                    section's bare typography while the same RTE content
                    on main-article (article.content) and main-page
                    (page.content) gets the unified .rte cascade — a
                    cross-template typography inconsistency that
                    reviewers flag explicitly. Skip the class on the
                    truncated branch because strip_html removes the rich
                    markup, leaving plain text where the cascade adds
                    nothing visible.
                  {%- endcomment -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.truncate -%}
                    {%- comment -%}
                      R87 — `truncatewords: block.settings.word_limit
                      | default: 40` parses as the `default` filter
                      operating on the (already-truncated) string,
                      not on `word_limit`. If the merchant clears
                      the word_limit setting, `truncatewords: nil`
                      raises a Liquid error or silently returns the
                      whole description. Pre-assign a safe local
                      so `default` lands on the variable.
                    {%- endcomment -%}
                    {%- assign word_limit_safe = block.settings.word_limit | default: 40 -%}
                    <div class="kt-pdp__short-desc" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                      {{ product.description | strip_html | truncatewords: word_limit_safe }}
                    </div>
                  {%- else -%}
                    <div class="kt-pdp__short-desc rte" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                      {{ product.description }}
                    </div>
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'variant_picker' -%}
                <div {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- render 'product-variant-picker', product: product -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'buy_buttons' -%}
                <div {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- comment -%}
                    Selling-plan picker is rendered INSIDE
                    snippets/product-form.liquid (R86 fix —
                    SUB-01 / SUB-03 require the `name="selling_plan"`
                    input to live inside `{% form 'product' %}`).
                    Previously the picker was a sibling render here
                    BEFORE product-form, which placed the input
                    outside the form and silently dropped
                    selling_plan from the cart payload on non-JS
                    submission + broke the JS plan-change handler
                    (its `closest('[data-product-form]')` returned
                    null because the wrapper hadn't opened yet).
                  {%- endcomment -%}
                  {%- render 'product-form', product: product, show_dynamic_checkout: false -%}
                  {%- comment -%}
                    Pickup availability — rendered directly beneath the
                    Add-to-Cart so merchants running a retail shopfront
                    alongside their online store surface BOPIS before
                    the customer scrolls past checkout. Only renders
                    when the variant has at least one pick-up-enabled
                    location; the snippet handles its own empty state.
                  {%- endcomment -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.show_pickup_availability -%}
                    {%- render 'pickup-availability', variant: product.selected_or_first_available_variant, product: product -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'trust_badges' -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__trust-badges" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- for i in (1..4) -%}
                    {%- assign icon_key = 'badge_' | append: i | append: '_icon' -%}
                    {%- assign text_key = 'badge_' | append: i | append: '_text' -%}
                    {%- assign icon_val = block.settings[icon_key] -%}
                    {%- assign text_val = block.settings[text_key] -%}
                    {%- if text_val != blank -%}
                      <div class="kt-pdp__trust-badge">
                        <svg aria-hidden="true" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                          {%- case icon_val -%}
                            {%- when 'shipping' -%}
                              <rect x="1" y="3" width="15" height="13"></rect><polygon points="16 8 20 8 23 11 23 16 16 16 16 8"></polygon><circle cx="5.5" cy="18.5" r="2.5"></circle><circle cx="18.5" cy="18.5" r="2.5"></circle>
                            {%- when 'returns' -%}
                              <polyline points="1 4 1 10 7 10"></polyline><path d="M3.51 15a9 9 0 1 0 2.13-9.36L1 10"></path>
                            {%- when 'warranty' -%}
                              <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
                            {%- when 'package' -%}
                              <line x1="16.5" y1="9.4" x2="7.5" y2="4.21"></line><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"></path>
                          {%- endcase -%}
                        </svg>
                        <span class="kt-pdp__trust-badge-text">{{ text_val }}</span>
                      </div>
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'accordion' -%}
                {%- capture accordion_content -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.page != blank -%}
                    {{ block.settings.page.content }}
                  {%- else -%}
                    {{ block.settings.content }}
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endcapture -%}
                <div {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- render 'product-accordion', title: block.settings.title, content: accordion_content, open: block.settings.open -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'door_sample' -%}
                {%- assign sample_product = block.settings.sample_product | default: product -%}
                {%- if sample_product != blank -%}
                  {%- assign sample_variant = sample_product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}
                  <div class="kt-pdp__door-sample" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                    <div class="kt-pdp__door-sample-header">
                      <span class="kt-pdp__door-sample-title">{{ block.settings.header_title | default: main_product_sample_header_default }}</span>
                      {%- if block.settings.ships_badge != blank -%}
                        <span class="kt-pdp__door-sample-badge">{{ block.settings.ships_badge }}</span>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    </div>
                    <div class="kt-pdp__door-sample-body">
                      <div class="kt-pdp__door-sample-info">
                        <h2 class="kt-pdp__door-sample-name">{{ sample_product.title }}</h2>
                        <div class="kt-pdp__door-sample-price">
                          <span>{{ sample_variant.price | money }}</span>
                          {%- if block.settings.refundable -%}
                            <span class="kt-pdp__door-sample-refundable">{{ 'kt.product.sample.refundable' | t | default: 'Refundable' }}</span>
                          {%- endif -%}
                        </div>
                        {%- if block.settings.description != blank -%}
                          <p class="kt-pdp__door-sample-desc">{{ block.settings.description }}</p>
                        {%- endif -%}
                      </div>
                      {%- form 'product', sample_product, id: 'DoorSampleForm-blk', class: 'kt-pdp__door-sample-form' -%}
                        <input type="hidden" name="id" value="{{ sample_variant.id }}">
                        <input type="hidden" name="quantity" value="1">
                        <button type="submit" class="kt-pdp__door-sample-btn" {% unless sample_variant.available %}disabled{% endunless %}>
                          {%- if sample_variant.available -%}
                            {{ block.settings.button_text | default: main_product_add_sample_default }}
                          {%- else -%}
                            {{ 'kt.product.sold_out' | t }}
                          {%- endif -%}
                        </button>
                      {%- endform -%}
                    </div>
                  </div>
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'concierge_box' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  CTA link resolution, in order of preference:
                    1. Merchant-picked `cta_link` (url type) — wins.
                    2. Store's Contact page via `pages.contact.url` —
                       carries the locale prefix for multi-language
                       stores and never 404s when the page doesn't
                       exist (resolves to blank, caught below).
                  We DO NOT hard-code '/pages/contact' as a fallback —
                  that path skips the routes object entirely, breaks
                  under localized URLs, and sends shoppers to a 404 on
                  any store whose contact page lives under a different
                  handle. If no URL can be resolved the link is hidden
                  instead of rendering a broken anchor.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- assign concierge_cta_url = block.settings.cta_link | default: pages.contact.url -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__concierge" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
                    <h2 class="kt-pdp__concierge-heading">{{ block.settings.heading }}</h2>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.body != blank -%}
                    <p class="kt-pdp__concierge-body">{{ block.settings.body }}</p>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if block.settings.cta_text != blank and concierge_cta_url != blank -%}
                    <a href="{{ concierge_cta_url | escape }}" class="kt-pdp__concierge-cta">
                      {{ block.settings.cta_text }}
                      {% render 'icon-arrow-right', width: 14, height: 14, stroke_width: 1.6 %}
                    </a>
                  {%- endif -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'spacer' -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__spacer" style="--kt-spacer-h: {{ block.settings.height | default: 16 }}px;" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}></div>

              {%- when 'complementary_products' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  R121 — Complementary products block. Shows manually-
                  curated complementary items inside the PDP info
                  column (separate from the algorithmic "related-
                  products" section that sits below the layout).

                  Data source: the
                  `shopify--discovery--product_recommendation.related_products`
                  metafield, populated via Shopify's Search &
                  Discovery app. Synchronous render — no async fetch
                  — because the metafield is available at PDP
                  render time.

                  Compact inline card markup (image + title + price)
                  rather than the full card-product snippet, because
                  the PDP info column is narrow (~360px on desktop)
                  and the full card's hover/swap/quote-button
                  affordances would feel cramped.

                  Empty-state matrix:
                    - Metafield populated → renders compact list.
                    - Metafield empty + design_mode → editor hint
                      pointing at Search & Discovery app.
                    - Metafield empty + live → block emits NOTHING.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  R149 COMPLEMENTARY-METAFIELD-1: read the
                  `complementary_products` metafield, not
                  `related_products`. Search & Discovery stores
                  curated complementary picks at
                  `shopify--discovery--product_recommendation.complementary_products`
                  — this block is named "complementary" so it must
                  read that key. Reading `related_products` was a
                  data mismatch (the same key as the related-products
                  section), so the "Pairs well with" block surfaced
                  related-not-complementary picks → reviewer flag
                  for misleading feature wiring.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- assign comp_products = product.metafields.shopify--discovery--product_recommendation.complementary_products.value -%}
                {%- if comp_products and comp_products.size > 0 -%}
                  <div class="kt-pdp__complementary" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                    {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
                      <h3 class="kt-pdp__complementary-heading">{{ block.settings.heading | escape }}</h3>
                    {%- endif -%}
                    <ul class="kt-pdp__complementary-list" role="list">
                      {%- for comp_product in comp_products limit: block.settings.products_count -%}
                        <li class="kt-pdp__complementary-item">
                          <a class="kt-pdp__complementary-link" href="{{ comp_product.url }}">
                            <div class="kt-pdp__complementary-media">
                              {%- if comp_product.featured_media != blank -%}
                                {{ comp_product.featured_media | image_url: width: 200 | image_tag:
                                    loading: 'lazy',
                                    widths: '100, 200, 300',
                                    sizes: '100px',
                                    width: 100,
                                    height: 100,
                                    class: 'kt-pdp__complementary-image',
                                    alt: comp_product.featured_media.alt | default: comp_product.title }}
                              {%- else -%}
                                {{ 'product-1' | placeholder_svg_tag: 'kt-pdp__complementary-image kt-pdp__complementary-image--placeholder' }}
                              {%- endif -%}
                            </div>
                            <div class="kt-pdp__complementary-text">
                              <p class="kt-pdp__complementary-title">{{ comp_product.title | escape }}</p>
                              {%- comment -%}
                                R86 SUB-05 — pre-format money before
                                t-interpolation so `| money` lands on
                                price_min, not on the t output.
                              {%- endcomment -%}
                              {%- if comp_product.price_varies -%}
                                {%- assign comp_price_money = comp_product.price_min | money -%}
                                <p class="kt-pdp__complementary-price">{{ 'kt.product.from_price_label' | t }} {{ comp_price_money }}</p>
                              {%- else -%}
                                <p class="kt-pdp__complementary-price">{{ comp_product.price | money }}</p>
                              {%- endif -%}
                            </div>
                          </a>
                        </li>
                      {%- endfor -%}
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                {%- elsif request.design_mode -%}
                  <div class="kt-pdp__complementary kt-pdp__complementary--empty" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                    <p class="kt-pdp__complementary-hint">
                      {{ 'kt.product.complementary.editor_hint' | t | default: 'Install the Shopify Search & Discovery app and pick complementary products for this product to populate this block.' }}
                    </p>
                  </div>
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'payment_icons' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  R120 — Payment-method icons block. Surfaces the
                  payment providers the merchant has enabled in
                  Shopify Payments / Stripe / etc. so shoppers see
                  trust signals (Visa, Mastercard, PayPal, Apple Pay)
                  next to the buy button.

                  `shop.enabled_payment_types` returns an array of
                  Shopify-emitted strings like 'visa', 'master',
                  'american_express', 'paypal', 'shopify_pay',
                  'apple_pay', 'google_pay'. The
                  `payment_type_svg_tag` filter outputs the
                  corresponding official SVG with proper a11y
                  attributes — no manual icon library needed and
                  the visuals stay current as Shopify adds providers.

                  When the merchant has zero enabled payment types
                  (rare — devstores during initial setup), the loop
                  renders nothing and the block is silently empty.
                  In design_mode we surface an editor hint so the
                  merchant knows what to configure.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__payment-icons" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
                    <p class="kt-pdp__payment-icons-heading">{{ block.settings.heading | escape }}</p>
                  {%- endif -%}
                  {%- if shop.enabled_payment_types.size > 0 -%}
                    <ul class="kt-pdp__payment-icons-list" role="list" aria-label="{{ 'kt.product.payment_icons.aria_label' | t | default: 'Accepted payment methods' }}">
                      {%- for type in shop.enabled_payment_types -%}
                        <li class="kt-pdp__payment-icon">
                          {{ type | payment_type_svg_tag: class: 'kt-pdp__payment-icon-svg' }}
                        </li>
                      {%- endfor -%}
                    </ul>
                  {%- elsif request.design_mode -%}
                    <p class="kt-pdp__payment-icons-hint">
                      {{ 'kt.product.payment_icons.editor_hint' | t | default: 'Enable payment providers in Shopify admin → Settings → Payments to populate this block.' }}
                    </p>
                  {%- endif -%}
                </div>

              {%- when 'metafield' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  R156 PDP-METAFIELD-BLOCK-1: surface arbitrary
                  product metafields without code edits. Theme Store
                  paid-tier expects merchants to render Material /
                  Dimensions / Care Instructions / Country of Origin
                  / Sustainability Notes etc. as info rows on the PDP
                  via a configurable block. Block accepts namespace
                  + key + visible label; reads
                  `product.metafields[ns][key]`. Renders only when
                  the metafield exists AND is non-blank — silent on
                  fresh installs without configuration.

                  Type-aware rendering via `metafield_tag`-like
                  fallback: pages/products/collections/files become
                  links via Shopify's auto-coercion of reference
                  metafields; rich_text / single_line_text /
                  multi_line_text render as text. The .value
                  accessor handles type-coercion for native types.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- assign mf_ns = block.settings.namespace | default: 'custom' -%}
                {%- assign mf_key = block.settings.key -%}
                {%- if mf_ns != blank and mf_key != blank -%}
                  {%- assign mf_value = product.metafields[mf_ns][mf_key].value -%}
                  {%- if mf_value != blank -%}
                    <div class="kt-pdp__metafield" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                      {%- if block.settings.label != blank -%}
                        <p class="kt-pdp__metafield-label">{{ block.settings.label | escape }}</p>
                      {%- endif -%}
                      <div class="kt-pdp__metafield-value">
                        {{- product.metafields[mf_ns][mf_key] -}}
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  {%- elsif request.design_mode -%}
                    {%- comment -%} Editor hint when block is unconfigured {%- endcomment -%}
                    <div class="kt-pdp__metafield kt-pdp__metafield--placeholder" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                      <p class="kt-pdp__metafield-hint">
                        {{ 'kt.product.metafield.editor_hint' | t | default: 'Configure namespace + key in the editor sidebar to surface a product metafield.' }}
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- elsif request.design_mode -%}
                  <div class="kt-pdp__metafield kt-pdp__metafield--placeholder" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                    <p class="kt-pdp__metafield-hint">
                      {{ 'kt.product.metafield.editor_hint' | t | default: 'Configure namespace + key in the editor sidebar to surface a product metafield.' }}
                    </p>
                  </div>
                {%- endif -%}

              {%- when 'liquid' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  Custom Liquid block — Theme Store requires Custom Liquid
                  blocks "wherever app blocks would be used". Sits next
                  to {%- when '@app' -%} so a merchant who needs to drop
                  in arbitrary Liquid (not packaged as an app extension)
                  has a first-class slot inside the PDP info column.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__custom-liquid" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {{ block.settings.custom_liquid }}
                </div>

              {%- when '@app' -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  R87 — wrap in shopify_attributes div so theme
                  editor can highlight + scroll-to the app block
                  on merchant click.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                <div class="kt-pdp__app-block" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                  {%- render block -%}
                </div>

            {%- endcase -%}
          {%- endfor -%}

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{%- comment -%}
  Sticky add-to-cart bar (R135 / CR-B). Rendered outside the section
  wrapper so it can position fixed-bottom across the entire viewport
  without being clipped by section padding. The snippet itself gates
  on `section.settings.show_sticky_atc` and product availability.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- render 'product-sticky-bar', product: product, section: section -%}

<script src="{{ 'product-gallery.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
<script src="{{ 'product-form.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
<script src="{{ 'countdown.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
<script src="{{ 'kt-section-main-product.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>

{%- comment -%}
  R285 — Recently-viewed tracker. The script is ALSO loaded by
  sections/recently-viewed-products.liquid (for the render
  branch — Phase 2). On its own it loaded ONLY on pages that
  carry the Recently Viewed rail, which meant the Phase 1
  tracker never ran when the merchant placed the rail on a
  home / collection / journal page but the customer was
  browsing PDPs without the rail. localStorage stayed empty
  and the rail had nothing to render even after dozens of
  product views.

  Loading it here AS WELL is safe — the script self-installs a
  `window.__kitcheroRecentlyViewedLoaded` guard at the top, so
  a second load (when both a PDP AND the rail are on the same
  page, or when the storefront uses both templates with the
  rail) is a no-op. The defer attribute means it never blocks
  paint. Tracker runs on DOMContentLoaded, reads the handle
  from `window.location.pathname`, and pushes it onto the
  `kt_viewed` array in localStorage. Subsequent visits to a
  page with the rail then have data to render.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script src="{{ 'recently-viewed.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
{%- comment -%}
  Selling-plan picker JS only emits when the product actually has
  subscription plans configured. Saves a ~1.5KB transfer on every
  non-subscription product page.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if product.selling_plan_groups.size > 0 -%}
  <script src="{{ 'selling-plan-picker.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
{%- endif -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Only load the product-model custom element registration when the
  product actually has 3D model media — avoids a no-op script request
  on products that only have 2D images. The <product-model> tag is
  only emitted by product-media-gallery.liquid when media.media_type
  equals 'model', so the registration is moot otherwise.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign has_3d_model = false -%}
{%- for media in product.media -%}
  {%- if media.media_type == 'model' -%}
    {%- assign has_3d_model = true -%}
    {%- break -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if has_3d_model -%}
  <script src="{{ 'product-model.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
{%- endif -%}

